            <person xml:id="pers0438">
               <p>A highly respected grocer and mercer, Colbeck was steward of the
                     <placeName>Keighley</placeName> Methodist society from <date when="1746"
                     >1746</date> until his death, and steward also of the
                     <placeName>Keighley</placeName> or <placeName>Haworth</placeName> circuit. In
                     <date when="1748">1748</date>
                  <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>Wesley</persName> accepted him as
                  an Assistant among his <seg ana="itinerancy">traveling preachers</seg>, though in
                  fact he was never stationed away from the <placeName>West Riding of
                     Yorkshire</placeName>. He served (and attended Conference occasionally) as one
                  of <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>Wesley</persName>&apos;s major
                  local preachers. See Vickers, <hi rend="italic">Dictionary</hi>, 73.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
